The Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation,
established by the co-founder of  Microsoft Corp. , added 17.9
million shares of  Berkshire Hathaway Inc.  in the third quarter,
according to a filing today with the U.S. Securities and
Exchange Commission.  The Seattle foundation added the shares as they gained 3.8
percent in the three months ended Sept. 30, making the holding
its largest, constituting 52 percent of the portfolio, the
filing shows.  Berkshire Hathaway is run by billionaire  Warren Buffett ,
whose fortune was estimated by Forbes magazine at about $45
billion. Most of it will go to the Gates Foundation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Gillian Wee  in New York at 
 gwee3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christian Baumgaertel at 
 cbaumgaertel@bloomberg.net . 